          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAORL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at the Oak Ridge",
                "National Laboratory Holifield Radioactive Ion Beam",
                "Facility.An inverse kinematics was chosen because",
                "enriched 15N targets can be difficult to fabricate",
                "while CD2 targets are readily available. The use of",
                "inverse kinematics allows measurements at the most",
                "forward center-of-mass angles where the cross section",
                "is most sensitive to the spectroscopic factors,"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "CD2 target with thickness of 90mu-g/cm2"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Scattered protons were detected in the large-area",
                "segmented silicon detector array (SIDAR).SIDAR is",
                "comprised of 128 segments with 16 radial (from 5 to",
                "13 cm) and 8 azimuthal divisions. The array covered",
                "backward laboratory angles 155deg -  169deg,",
                "corresponding  to 3deg - 8deg in CMS. allowing",
                "detection of the forward focused scattered protons."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In part of the measurement, the heavy 16N",
                "recoils were detected in coincidence with protons",
                "by  Daresbury Recoil Separator, consisting of two",
                "Wien filters, dipole segment and three quadrupole",
                "triplets."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Protons emitted close to 90 deg were",
                "detected by ORRUBA array, consisting of two rings if",
                "Si strip detectors. Forward angle ring consist of",
                "detector telescopes with detectors of thickness of",
                "65 mu-m for dE measurement and detector with thickness",
                "of 1000 mu-m as stopping detector. The backward angle",
                "rings comprised of a single layer of 500 mu-m thick",
                "resistive strip detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
